<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1338,2013]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1699,1725]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of the new species reflects the fact that the larva develops inside the stem of 
<taxonomicName box="[1343,1436,1699,1725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Achillea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Achillea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(“achillea”— 
<taxonomicName box="[300,393,1735,1761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Achillea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[300,393,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Achillea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “caulis”—stem).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
